3.40	Idiot's_Delight_(film)	Idiot's Delight (film)	Idiot's Delight is a 1939 MGM comedy-drama with a screenplay adapted by Robert E. Sherwood from his 1936 Pulitzer-Prize-winning play of the same name. The movie showcases Clark Gable, a major star of the period, and Norma Shearer in the declining phase of her career. Although not a musical, it is notable as the only film where Gable sings and dances, performing "Puttin' on the Ritz" by Irving Berlin.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b7/IdiotsDelight1939.jpg/220px-IdiotsDelight1939.jpg
